{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17646880","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17646880"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:36:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:36:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18211"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18211"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.17,0.13,0,0.63]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10925"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77627"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10925","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10925"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18211"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63140"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4936"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5253"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25396"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25400"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77627","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77627"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a follow-up appointment. She has a history of systemic lupus erythematosus and is currently being treated with prednisolone, azathioprine, and hydroxychloroquine. Despite this regimen, she continues to experience significant disease activity. Her rheumatologist is considering adding a medication that inhibits B-lymphocyte stimulator protein to her treatment plan.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications is an inhibitor of B-lymphocyte stimulator protein that can be used as an add-on therapy in this case?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Etanercept","Belimumab","Anakinra","Abatacept","Rituximab"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBelimumab\u003C/strong\u003E is a monoclonal antibody that specifically inhibits B-lymphocyte stimulator protein (BLyS), also known as B-cell activating factor (BAFF). It is used as an add-on therapy in patients with systemic lupus erythematosus who have not responded adequately to standard treatments such as prednisolone, azathioprine, methotrexate, and hydroxychloroquine.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEtanercept\u003C/strong\u003E is a tumour necrosis factor (TNF) inhibitor used primarily in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and other inflammatory conditions, but it does not target B-lymphocyte stimulator protein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnakinra\u003C/strong\u003E is an interleukin-1 receptor antagonist used in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis and other inflammatory conditions, but it does not inhibit B-lymphocyte stimulator protein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAbatacept\u003C/strong\u003E is a selective T-cell co-stimulation modulator used in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis, but it does not target B-lymphocyte stimulator protein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERituximab\u003C/strong\u003E is a monoclonal antibody that targets CD20 on B cells, leading to B cell depletion. While it affects B cells, it does not specifically inhibit B-lymphocyte stimulator protein.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Belimumab is a monoclonal antibody that inhibits B-lymphocyte stimulator protein, used in the treatment of systemic lupus erythematosus.","Belimumab is often used as an add-on therapy to standard treatments like prednisolone, azathioprine, methotrexate, and hydroxychloroquine.","Inhibiting B-lymphocyte stimulator protein can help reduce the activity of B cells, which are involved in the pathogenesis of autoimmune diseases."],"references":["Padda IS, Goyal A. Leflunomide. 2023 Jun 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491731","Tian H, Cronstein BN. Understanding the mechanisms of action of methotrexate: implications for the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis. Bull NYU Hosp Jt Dis. 2007;65(3):168-73. PMID: 17922664","Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809527","Singh JA, Shah NP, Mudano AS. Belimumab for systemic lupus erythematosus. Cochrane Database Syst Rev. 2021 Feb 25;2(2):CD010668. doi: 10.1002/14651858.CD010668.pub2. PMID: 33631841; PMCID: PMC8095005.","Blair HA, Duggan ST. Belimumab: A Review in Systemic Lupus Erythematosus. Drugs. 2018 Mar;78(3):355-366. doi: 10.1007/s40265-018-0872-z. PMID: 29396833."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63140"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18211"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63140","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63140"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T20:42:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T20:43:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10925"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77627"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":